</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[187,1400,1539,2025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName authority="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane, 2021" authorityName="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,409,1539,1565]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="souvannii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,409,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Sonerila souvannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[416,506,1539,1565]" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Cho" authorityYear="2020" box="[655,867,1539,1565]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardamomensis">
<emphasis box="[655,867,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">S. cardamomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1189,1539,1565]" name="Cambodia" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
, in its acaulescent habit and in the shape of its leaves, but it differs in the shape of its rhizome (cylindrical in 
<taxonomicName box="[1269,1398,1574,1600]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="souvanii">
<emphasis box="[1269,1398,1574,1600]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">S. souvanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs bulbous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. H. Cho" authorityYear="2020" box="[358,574,1609,1636]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardamomensis">
<emphasis box="[358,574,1609,1636]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">S. cardamomensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), larger leaves (8â€“10 Ã— 
<quantity box="[864,953,1609,1636]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="cm" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“9 cm</quantity>
vs 1â€“4 Ã— 
<quantity box="[1076,1213,1610,1636]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="cm" value="1.8" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="0.9">0.9â€“2.7 cm</quantity>
), petiole length and color (
<quantity box="[322,428,1645,1672]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8â€“15 cm</quantity>
long and light green vs 
<quantity box="[726,860,1645,1672]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="cm" value="1.45" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4â€“2.5 cm</quantity>
long and reddish brown), greater number of flowers per cyme (20â€“25 vs 5â€“11), and petal length and pubescence (9â€“10 Ã— 
<quantity box="[1106,1204,1680,1707]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“7 mm</quantity>
and glabrous vs 5.5â€“6 Ã— 
<quantity box="[286,406,1715,1742]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5â€“4 mm</quantity>
with glandular trichomes on midveins abaxially). 
<taxonomicName authority="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane, 2021" authorityName="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane" authorityYear="2021" box="[998,1219,1715,1741]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="souvannii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[998,1219,1715,1741]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Sonerila souvannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1227,1317,1716,1742]" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[304,538,1751,1777]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dongnathamensis">
<emphasis box="[304,538,1751,1777]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">S. dongnathamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[607,711,1751,1777]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Thailand</collectingCountry>
in the shape of its inflorescences, but differs in the rhizome shape (cylindrical vs globose), the shape of the leaf base (cordate vs obtuse to rounded), pedicel length (
<quantity box="[198,326,1821,1848]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="10.0">10â€“25 mm</quantity>
long vs 
<quantity box="[427,525,1822,1848]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€“4 mm</quantity>
long), the number of flowers per cyme (20â€“25 vs 5â€“12), and in the length and outline of the petals (9â€“10 Ã— 
<quantity box="[578,678,1857,1883]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“7 mm</quantity>
, acute vs 3â€“5 Ã— 
<quantity box="[868,968,1857,1883]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“4 mm</quantity>
, acuminate with long seta). The new species is also related to 
<taxonomicName box="[475,606,1892,1919]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuberosa">
<emphasis box="[475,606,1892,1919]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">S. tuberosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[675,799,1892,1918]" name="Cambodia" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
, but distinguished in the rhizome shape (cylindrical vs slightly bulbous), the shape of the leaf base (cordate vs very broadly ovate to orbicular), pedicel length (
<quantity box="[196,324,1963,1990]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="10.0">10â€“25 mm</quantity>
long vs 
<quantity box="[420,516,1963,1990]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“6 mm</quantity>
long), the number of flowers per cyme (20â€“25 vs 4â€“8), and in the length and outline of the petals (9â€“10 Ã— 
<quantity box="[528,628,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“7 mm</quantity>
, acute vs 5 Ã— 
<quantity box="[788,881,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
, elliptic, apiculate, pink) (
<tableCitation box="[1186,1277,1998,2024]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="6.[189,259,265,291]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Table 2. Comparison of Sonerila souvannii Phonep. &amp; Soulad. sp. nov., S. cardamomensis S.H.Cho, S. dongnathamensis Suddee, Phutthai &amp; Rueangr., and S. tuberosa C.Hansen. 1 = from Sinh et al. 2020; 2 = from Suddee et al. 2014; 3 = from Hansen 1989." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF29FB9A2410FFACFF79222AFCBB4D48" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" tableUuid="DF29FB9A2410FFACFF79222AFCBB4D48">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
