<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="143" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,637,1502,1528]" box="[189,637,1502,1528]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,637,1502,1528]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,637,1502,1528]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">Distribution, habitat and phenology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1550,1724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicName authority="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane, 2021" authorityName="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,413,1550,1576]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="souvannii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,413,1550,1576]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">Sonerila souvannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[422,515,1551,1577]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
grows in loose soil in the crevices of shaded rocks at 
<quantity box="[1171,1307,1550,1577]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" unit="m" value="205.0" valueMax="210.0" valueMin="200.0">200â€“210 m</quantity>
a.s.l. It grows in the understorey of lowland semi-evergreen forest together with 
<taxonomicName authority="A. DC." authorityName="A. DC." box="[1060,1399,1587,1613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martabanica">
<emphasis box="[1060,1315,1587,1613]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">Begonia martabanica</emphasis>
A.DC.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="C. Agardh" authorityName="C. Agardh" box="[197,480,1624,1651]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Begoniaceae C.Agardh</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(C. Hansen) Cellin. &amp; S. S. Renner" authorityName="Cellin. &amp; S. S. Renner" baseAuthorityName="C. Hansen" box="[504,1173,1624,1650]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Phyllagathis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuberosa">
<emphasis box="[504,766,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">Phyllagathis tuberosa</emphasis>
(C.Hansen) Cellin. &amp; S.S.Renner
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Juss." authorityName="Juss." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Melastomataceae Juss.</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[317,560,1661,1687]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="denticulata">
<emphasis box="[317,560,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">Davallia denticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Burm. f.) Mett. ex Kuhn (
<taxonomicName authority="M. R. Schomb. ex A. B. Frank" authorityName="A. B. Frank" box="[887,1386,1661,1688]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Davalliaceae M.R.Schomb. ex A.B.Frank</taxonomicName>
). Flowering and fruiting in September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="143" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,587,1765,1791]" box="[189,587,1765,1791]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,587,1765,1791]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,587,1765,1791]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">Preliminary conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[187,1400,1813,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">
We found three small sub-populations of 
<taxonomicName authority="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane, 2021" authorityName="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane" authorityYear="2021" box="[660,800,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="souvannii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[660,800,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="143">S. souvannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[806,895,1814,1840]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with each comprising only 5â€“6 individuals, about 
<quantity box="[262,322,1851,1877]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" unit="m" value="20.0">20 m</quantity>
apart. The species has not yet been found anywhere else. Considering the species grows in a very narrowly restricted area where human activity, such as collection of non-timber forest products (NTFPs) and the logging of wood for local uses, can be seen, we need to pay attention to its conservation. As the number of mature individuals is less than 50, we assess this species as Critical Endangered (CR) criteria D (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standard &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[316,461,1998,2024]" pageId="7" pageNumber="143" refId="ref5489" refString="IUCN Standard and Petitions Committee. 2019. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee. Available from https: // www. iucnredlist. org / resources / redlistguidelines [accessed on 2 Sep. 2020]." type="url" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
